#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn6.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn6.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The Appeal "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 6. Brahmalokasutta → pamādasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts2) | pamādaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn6.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Brahmalokasutta "
msgstr "6. The Negligent Brahmā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.147, pts2ed1.319, sc1
msgctxt "sn6.6:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā divāvihāragato hoti paṭisallīno. "
msgstr "Now at that time the Buddha had gone into retreat for the day’s meditation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: paccekaṃ dvārabāhaṃ → paccekadvārabāhaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn6.6:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho subrahmā ca paccekabrahmā suddhāvāso ca paccekabrahmā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā paccekaṃ dvārabāhaṃ upanissāya aṭṭhaṃsu. Atha kho subrahmā paccekabrahmā suddhāvāsaṃ paccekabrahmānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the independent brahmās Subrahmā and Suddhāvāsa went to the Buddha and stationed themselves one by each door-post. But Subrahmā said to Suddhāvāsa, "

msgctxt "sn6.6:1.4"
msgid "“akālo kho tāva, mārisa, bhagavantaṃ payirupāsituṃ; "
msgstr "“Good sir, it’s the wrong time to pay homage to the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn6.6:1.5"
msgid "divāvihāragato bhagavā paṭisallīno ca. "
msgstr "He has gone into retreat for the day’s meditation. "

msgctxt "sn6.6:1.6"
msgid "Asuko ca brahmaloko iddho ceva phīto ca, brahmā ca tatra pamādavihāraṃ viharati. "
msgstr "But such and such Brahmā realm is successful and prosperous, while the Brahmā living there is negligent. "

msgctxt "sn6.6:1.7"
msgid "Āyāma, mārisa, yena so brahmaloko tenupasaṅkamissāma; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ brahmānaṃ saṃvejeyyāmā”ti. "
msgstr "Come, let’s go to that Brahmā realm and inspire awe in that Brahmā!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:1.8"
msgid "“Evaṃ, mārisā”ti kho suddhāvāso paccekabrahmā subrahmuno paccekabrahmuno paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, good sir,” replied Suddhāvāsa. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.320, sc2
msgctxt "sn6.6:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho subrahmā ca paccekabrahmā suddhāvāso ca paccekabrahmā—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso … pe … evameva—bhagavato purato antarahitā tasmiṃ brahmaloke pāturahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, they vanished from in front of the Buddha and appeared in that Brahmā realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:2.2"
msgid "Addasā kho so brahmā te brahmāno dūratova āgacchante. Disvāna te brahmāno etadavoca: "
msgstr "That Brahmā saw those Brahmās coming off in the distance and said to them, "

msgctxt "sn6.6:2.3"
msgid "“handa kuto nu tumhe, mārisā, āgacchathā”ti? "
msgstr "“Well now, good sirs, where have you come from?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:2.4"
msgid "“Āgatā kho mayaṃ, mārisa, amha tassa bhagavato santikā arahato sammāsambuddhassa. "
msgstr "“Good sir, we’ve come from the presence of the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha. "

# NOTE: I agree with MS here as opposed to BB, it feels more like a question here, cp. say AN 6.62
msgctxt "sn6.6:2.5"
msgid "Gaccheyyāsi pana tvaṃ, mārisa, tassa bhagavato upaṭṭhānaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā”ti? "
msgstr "Shouldn’t you go to attend on that Blessed One?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: Evaṃ vutto → evaṃ vutte (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn6.6:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutto, kho so brahmā taṃ vacanaṃ anadhivāsento sahassakkhattuṃ attānaṃ abhinimminitvā subrahmānaṃ paccekabrahmānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When they had spoken, that Brahmā refused to accept their advice. He multiplied himself a thousand times and said to Subrahmā, "

msgctxt "sn6.6:3.2"
msgid "“passasi me no tvaṃ, mārisa, evarūpaṃ iddhānubhāvan”ti? "
msgstr "“Good sir, can’t you see that I have such psychic power?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:3.3"
msgid "“Passāmi kho tyāhaṃ, mārisa, evarūpaṃ iddhānubhāvan”ti. "
msgstr "“I see that, good sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:3.4"
msgid "“So khvāhaṃ, mārisa, evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo kassa aññassa samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā upaṭṭhānaṃ gamissāmī”ti? "
msgstr "“Since I have such psychic power and might, what other ascetic or brahmin should I go to and attend upon?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.321, sc4
msgctxt "sn6.6:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho subrahmā paccekabrahmā dvisahassakkhattuṃ attānaṃ abhinimminitvā taṃ brahmānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Subrahmā multiplied himself two thousand times and said to that Brahmā, "

msgctxt "sn6.6:4.2"
msgid "“passasi me no tvaṃ, mārisa, evarūpaṃ iddhānubhāvan”ti? "
msgstr "“Good sir, can’t you see that I have such psychic power?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:4.3"
msgid "“Passāmi kho tyāhaṃ, mārisa, evarūpaṃ iddhānubhāvan”ti. "
msgstr "“I see that, good sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:4.4"
msgid "“Tayā ca kho, mārisa, mayā ca sveva bhagavā mahiddhikataro ceva mahānubhāvataro ca. "
msgstr "“That Buddha has even more psychic power and might than you or me. "

msgctxt "sn6.6:4.5"
msgid "Gaccheyyāsi tvaṃ, mārisa, tassa bhagavato upaṭṭhānaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā”ti? "
msgstr "Shouldn’t you go to attend on that Blessed One?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.6:4.6"
msgid "Atha kho so brahmā subrahmānaṃ paccekabrahmānaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then that Brahmā addressed Subrahmā in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.148, sc5
msgctxt "sn6.6:5.1"
msgid "“Tayo supaṇṇā caturo ca haṃsā, "
msgstr "“There are three hundreds of phoenixes, four of swans, and five of eagles. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.6:5.2"
msgid "Byagghīnisā pañcasatā ca jhāyino; "
msgstr "This palace belongs to him who practiced absorption. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: jalate ca → jalati ca (si) | jalateva (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn6.6:5.3"
msgid "Tayidaṃ vimānaṃ jalate ca brahme, "
msgstr "It shines, Brahmā, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.6:5.4"
msgid "Obhāsayaṃ uttarassaṃ disāyan”ti. "
msgstr "lighting up the northern quarter!” "

# NOTE: Taking jalate here as optative, in the previous as middle active (if it isn’t in fact jalati)
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.322, sc6
msgctxt "sn6.6:6.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi te taṃ jalate vimānaṃ, "
msgstr "“So what if your palace shines, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.6:6.2"
msgid "Obhāsayaṃ uttarassaṃ disāyaṃ; "
msgstr "lighting up the northern quarter? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.6:6.3"
msgid "Rūpe raṇaṃ disvā sadā pavedhitaṃ, "
msgstr "A clever person who has seen the deficiency in form, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.6:6.4"
msgid "Tasmā na rūpe ramatī sumedho”ti. "
msgstr "its chronic trembling, takes no pleasure in it.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn6.6:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho subrahmā ca paccekabrahmā suddhāvāso ca paccekabrahmā taṃ brahmānaṃ saṃvejetvā tatthevantaradhāyiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then after inspiring awe in that Brahmā, the independent brahmās Subrahmā and Suddhāvāsa vanished right there. "

msgctxt "sn6.6:7.2"
msgid "Agamāsi ca kho so brahmā aparena samayena bhagavato upaṭṭhānaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassāti. "
msgstr "And after some time that Brahmā went to attend on the Buddha."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
